Modifications
-------------

This Adapted Material modifies the original work as follows:

  * Reframed the project from a single-article research template into a
    multi-post personal-blog scaffolding.
  * Added a Home page (`src/pages/index.astro`) with an avatar, slogan,
    news feed, and a list of latest posts.
  * Added a Blog index page (`src/pages/blog.astro`).
  * Added an About page (`src/pages/about.astro`) with placeholder
    content.
  * Added a Browse page (`src/pages/browse.astro`) with client-side
    search, tag and category filters, and a year archive.
  * Added a generic site header/footer (`src/components/Header.astro`,
    `src/components/SiteFooter.astro`).
  * Added utilities for article discovery and date formatting
    (`src/utils/site-articles.ts`, `src/utils/article-modified.ts`,
    `src/utils/date-format.ts`, `src/utils/browse-links.ts`).
  * Added RSS and sitemap endpoints (`src/pages/rss.xml.js`,
    `src/pages/sitemap-index.xml.js`).
  * Added a typed content collection schema (`src/content.config.ts`)
    documenting the article frontmatter.
  * Replaced the upstream `package.json` metadata, removed the
    `release:*` scripts, and switched the SPDX license identifier to
    `CC-BY-4.0`.
  * Replaced the production `site` URL in `astro.config.mjs` with a
    placeholder.
  * Slimmed `src/content/bibliography.bib` to only the entries cited by
    the bundled demo article.
  * Generalized site-wide constants (`src/consts.ts`), the news feed
    (`src/data/site-news.ts`), and the About page into reusable
    placeholders.
  * Added a placeholder avatar (`public/avatar.svg`) and a generic
    `public/robots.txt`.
  * Removed personal-site artifacts: avatar JPGs, custom CNAME, Google
    Search Console verification file, WeChat QR, etc.
  * Added this NOTICE file and a new README focused on template usage.

Per CC BY 4.0 §3(a)(1)(B), this is sufficient notice that the work has
been modified. The bundled showcase article in `src/content/demo/` is
substantially unchanged and retains its original credit line.


Downstream attribution
----------------------

If you build a website on top of this template and publish it, please
keep:

  1. A link in your site footer (the default `SiteFooter.astro` already
     credits Thibaud's research-article-template).
  2. This `NOTICE` file in your repository if you redistribute the
     source.

You do *not* have to credit anyone in the rendered articles you write
yourself — those are entirely your own work. The attribution
requirement is only for the template scaffolding and any portion of
the demo article you keep.
